Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: Regarging NASAA ‚ÄúInternational Crypto Crackdown‚Äù  Yesterday we were contacted by Office of Missouri Secretary of State Securities Division with an Order to Cease & Desist and Order to Show Cause.  We would like to make a statement, that no USA (including all territories of this country) residents are allowed to obtain BALT tokens and participate in Baltic.fund campaigns, and here is how we eliminate them from taking part:  1. As a first step, everyone, who would like to join our community, no matter whether this person wants to purchase tokens or participate in our bounty campaign has to register at our website and sign the Terms between our company and himself/herself. Simply reading our Whitepaper is not enough. The only legal agreement between us and the token holders are Terms of Use, every participant of our ecosystem must register at our website, read and accept the Terms, otherwise he is not allowed to take part in any Baltic.fund activities.  It is clearly stated in our Terms of Use, that no USA (including all territories of this country) residents are allowed to obtain BALT tokens.  2. But that‚Äôs obviously not enough, that‚Äôs why we run KYC procedures on every person, who is registered at our website. Our KYC policy is very strict (and recently we explained why)and the KYC is mandatory for every token holder, no matter if a person purchased the tokens or receive them for the participation in our bounty campaign. In case, we have any doubts, we run additional KYC (including, but not limited to a video call with this person), and in case we still have doubts, we ban this person from receiving our tokens.  We take all these measures to be sure, that we comply with all the laws and regulations.  Also, we would like to point out, that our Whitepaper, Summary and other materials, including the articles on how our platform works, are advertising materials, and they don‚Äôt explain the legal regulations between us and our token holders. We oblige our community to read and agree to the Terms of Use.  In conclusion, we would like to add, that as it is stated above, there is no possibility for USA (including all territories of this country) residents to purchase, obtain, or somehow recieve BALT tokens.  https://medium.com/@baltic.fund/regarging-nasaa-international-crypto-crackdown-66e2849c6262

Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: KYC and bounty tokens distribution  Dear bounty supporters,  We are planning to start the token distribution for the bounty supporters next week. Only 20% of you passed the KYC for the bounty program participants. To make the process quick and clear for you, we created the following list.  How to know that you passed the KYC? Please, check the status in your personal account and in the spreadsheet. You can find the KYC status in the left bottom corner in your personal account. For those, who had some issues with automated KYC, your current status is available in the spreadsheet only. If you see the ‚ÄúPassed‚Äù status, then everything is ok and no need to worry, your tokens will be transferred to you during the next week.  If you haven‚Äôt started with KYC yet, here is what you do: ‚Äì Register at the baltic.fund website ‚Äì Confirm the registration via your e-mail ‚Äì Press the KYC button in your personal account and follow the instructions Please, keep in mind that by registering at the website and ticking the boxes you agree that you are not a citizen/resident of the USA and its territories. Also, please pay attention, that your name and surname at the registration must coincide with the name in your ID and your ID must be of an international type with a photo, otherwise, you won‚Äôt pass the automated KYC.  In case, you can‚Äôt pass the automated KYC, please, send a message to support@baltic.fund where you describe your problem. The title should look like ‚ÄúProblem with automated KYC‚Äù. Please, don‚Äôt send the messages like ‚ÄúImportant‚Äù in the title and ‚ÄúKYC?‚Äù in the message body, such kind of messages will have the lowest priority.  Please, don‚Äôt share your personal data in our official telegram channel, we delete messages of this type immediately because it‚Äôs not secure.  Good luck with KYC and thank you for being with us.  https://medium.com/@baltic.fund/kyc-and-bounty-tokens-distribution-b616a1c19d2

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: https://preview.ibb.co/mEQjWc/photo_2018_04_02_22_32_32.jpg  How platform helps investors?  Firstly, we pre-select the most promising startups out of thousands. We use an AI-based analysis tool to narrow the list, but the final preselection is up to industry experts. The platform offers the investors, which startups to support, based on their investment background, personal preferences, and exit strategy. The platform manages the whole acceleration process and paperwork, offering the investor weekly results of the acceleration. During the last 4 weeks of the acceleration, startups are introduced to matching seed/A-round investors worldwide. The early investors decide either they convert their options or sell them to the seed/ A-round investor(s) and exit. The platform offers the investors recommendations and projections based on predictive analysis, AI and experts opinions.  So, what it has to do with the ICO?  Acceleration program costs a certain amount of BALT tokens for each startup, depending on the startup score. We sell these tokens to investors during our ICO. Investor uses these tokens to fund a startup(s) acceleration. Startup(s) offers investor (s) an option, which can later be converted into equity share or sold to the next investor during the seed funding round.  How does the blockchain fit here?  Our goal is to make the whole process from pre-selection to exit totally transparent for every investor. Investor will be able to track each step and each stage of startup acceleration and later to track all the offers from potential seed/A-round investors.  How do we pre-select startups?  ‚Äì working MVP, traction, paying users  ‚Äì realistic business model  ‚Äì english-speaking founders with at least some entrepreneurial experience  ‚Äì trending industries: cybersecurity, enterprise, blockchain, AI/ML, edtech, fintech, energy, shared economy, and others How are we doing so far  ‚Äì 60 000 000 tokens are sold to the whitelisted crypto holders or committed by the professional investors during the private/public pre-ICOs  ‚Äì the application process for startups launches in the middle of April  ‚Äì several strategic partnerships with global corporations on startup mentoring  READ MORE

Body: Regardless to the fact that many citizens of CIS countries speak the same language, they have cultural differences, and these differences are considerable. Do you take it into account?

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: It would be really interesting to know how this question came up to you  Well, we do and we don't. When we do the startup scouting, we definitely keep in mind the cultural differences, however, when we pre-select the teams to join our accelerator, judge the pitching sessions, and interview startups ‚Äì our main concern is how open-minded and multicultural the team members are. We want our startups to join the global market and to become the market leaders, which means that they have to be able to quickly integrate into different cultures.  By now we have startups from 7 or 8 different countries in our accelerator, and I believe, that one of the main advantages of these teams and its members is an ability to learn from others and to cooperate, despite the cultural differences.

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: Well, interesting question, it depends what country you are talking about and what types of startups are there. First of all, you are right, there are more opportunities for startups in big cities: community, events, accelerators, mentors, etc. However, I can name several examples, when a startup from relatively small town became a global leader (check Ultimate guitar from Kaliningrad, Russia) and, also, when a small city started to develop infrastructure for startups and talents and became a local startup hub (check Tartu in Estonia).  I believe, what really matters, is not the town, where the startup was born, but the team and idea. But startups that are launched in bigger cities have more competitive advantages from the very beginning.  Partly, our platform will solve this problem for startups from small cities: they will be offered an online acceleration, which means that they will have nearly the same opportunities like startups from big cities, but online: mentorship, community, acceleration programs, access to funding.

There is quite a detailed description of what we expect from startups that join us. If you feel, that we are a match, fill in the form below and our startup manager will schedule an introduction call with you. Be ready to pitch your product When it comes to platform, you have to wait a bit until we launch it, it will happen in May-June (the first version of the platform).

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: We changed our smart-contract and extended the pre-sale period!  This article is very important, please, check it.  How our smart-contract worked before: BALT tokens from our wallet were automatically sent to every person who completed the KYC, was approved by our KYC team, and purchased tokens.  What were the problems: 1. Exchange wallets owners experienced problems with receiving tokens. Despite we warned our supporters, that tokens should be purchased from Ethereum wallets only (like MEW), we still received quite a number of transactions from exchange wallets. What happened after, is that tokens were lost at their way (and, sometimes, even the payments were lost and we had to deal with the exchange customers support), because they were sent back automatically. 2. Complaints about KYC, the majority of our users wanted to make a payment in order to ‚Äúreserve‚Äù tokens, and complete the KYC afterward. 3. No opportunities for Bitcoin owners.  Important notice! Everyone, who already purchased our tokens‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääyou have nothing to worry about. We have the list of all your wallets, so new BALT tokens will be transferred to you during the next 24 hours.  Also, the pre-sale period is extended to March 26, 2018, so you will have enough time to buy tokens.  So, how it works now after we deployed new smart contract.  We changed the order of actions for KYC (but we still require it).  You still have to do the KYC to receive tokens, but now you have an opportunity to pay for the token first and to complete KYC during the next 90 days.  So, how it works now: 1. You complete KYC, you are eligible to buy our tokens, your profile is confirmed. We sent BALT tokens to the Ethereum wallet from your website profile. 2. You complete KYC, you are not eligible to buy our tokens. You get notified by the e-mail and in your profile, and we make the refund. 3. You don‚Äôt complete KYC in 90 days. We will remind you every week, that you have to complete the KYC, however, if you fail to upload 2 documents and fill in 6 fields in 90 days, you won‚Äôt receive tokens and we won‚Äôt make a refund.  We added new payment methods and the tokens are sent manually now.  1. You have Ethereum wallet. The simplest case for both‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääyou and us. You register on the website, purchase the tokens, complete the KYC and we send tokens back to your wallet.  2. You have exchange wallet. You register on the website, choose ‚Äúexchange wallet‚Äù as a payment method and follow the instructions. After you complete the KYC, you still have to add any ETH wallet to your personal account on baltic.fund, so we could transfer BALT tokens to you.  3. You have Bitcoin wallet. You register on the website, choose ‚Äúbitcoin wallet‚Äù as a payment method and follow the instructions. After you complete the KYC, you still have to add any ETH wallet to your personal account on baltic.fund, so we could transfer BALT tokens to you.  4. You want to pay in EUR/USD. That‚Äôs fine, many of our investors, especially funds do this. Contact us at support@baltic.fund with the topic ‚ÄúToken purchase‚Äù and you will be redirected to the right guy.  Do you have any questions?  Join us on Facebook, Twitter, Telegram community, BitcoinTalk, or subscribe to our Medium blog.  Want to support our project?  Join our Bounty programs for translators, proofreaders, media influencers, and supporters. By participating in our Bounty campaign, you become part of the Baltic.fund community and help us create a robust and strong Platform and Ecosystem. Find out more at BitcoinTalk.  Want to become a part of our community?  Purchase our tokens with 15% bonus now!  https://medium.com/@baltic.fund/we-changed-our-smart-contract-and-extended-the-pre-sale-period-1d823ed8a668

Body: Hi, we have both types of money in our business cycle: fiats and crypto. We are more similar to traditional venture business, our model is clear to traditional investors (like VCs), so, if they would like to invest in fiats, we don't mind. By the way, we have several commitments with VCs for about 50M tokens, and partly these commitments are in fiats. The second reason for us not to be crypto focused is volatility. We are not crypto traders, our business is different, so fiat money is less risky.  Anyway, we accept both, ETH and fiats, it's up to you to choose.

Body: WEBSITE | TELEGRAM | TWITTER | FACEBOOK | MEDIUM | DISCORD  We are proud to present BALTIC.FUND INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS VIA BALTIC BLOCKCHAIN FUND  https://image.ibb.co/gqCWCS/bounty_OVER.jpg  BALTIC FUND BOUNTY PROGRAM - CLICK HERE  Translations:  Arabic translation Chinese translation Croatian translation Filipino translation French translation German translation Indonesian translation Italian translation Korean translation Malaysian translation Polish translation Portuguese translation Romanian translation Russian translation Spanish translation Turkish translation Ukrainian translation Vietnamese translation     Who we are  https://image.ibb.co/htHpLx/2018_02_21_3.png  We are accelerator and VC, growing the most promising Baltics and CIS startups from the very pre-seed to A stage. We invest in hardware and robotics, cybersecurity, enterprise software, fintech, AI and blockchain based projects.  We are also building the platform, where every token-holder gets access to the ecosystem and all the resources that help a startup to grow: mentorship, experts, media, legal services, marketing, PR, development, and investments.  How it works Let's crowd-incubate the startups!  We are building the platform, where you support the startups you like with BALT tokens and get perks or income for doing this. Be the first one to get the unique products and other benefits from the most promising CEE and CIS startups!  All the startups, registered at the platform, post a token investors proposal:  - how many tokens do they need - what do they need them for (development, production, marketing, etc.) - what would they offer their backers in return  So, what startups can offer you for your support:  - their products and services - partnership and collaboration (help with some of your tasks) - tokenized loan (they take your tokens, and give them back to you with multiplication after a certain period, buying BALT tokens at a public crypto exchange)  How startups can participate:  - offline, using our incubator space and its production facilities - online, using our services and partners facilities  How does Baltic Fund and BHV incubator help startups for the tokens you invested:  - incubation program with the experts from EU and the US, and our own mentors - production and engineering facilities, other incubator‚Äôs office opportunities - BHV.Labs‚Äô developers, designers, marketers, PR pros, analysts, engineers, etc. - venture partners - and the growing number of new opportunities!  What happens after the incubation:  - startups launch their products (and the contributor gets one) - startups grow and develop (and the price of your investments grow)  An investor gets product and income, a startup develops, we help and manage. Profit!  Additional benefits  Tech guys and experts Become a part of the community and collect all the perks: huge discounts or even free tickets to tech events worldwide, discounts in partners' co-working worldwide, discounts on software. Share your experience and earn additional tokens on the platform.  Crypto maniacs The price of a token will constantly grow during the next several years while the capitalization of startups is growing. Trade your tokens at stock exchanges or at the community and earn.  Startup founders and future startupers Become a part of an awesome community and ecosystem: get access to mentors, investors, events, use your tokens to gain PR, marketing, and development services from experts worldwide, and help your startup to grow. If you want to pivot your existing startup, or even more - you are new in this world, and just have an idea? Become a part of the community, find yourself a team from any part of the world and rock it!  Professional investors Contact us to find out more about our startup pipeline. Next unicorn might be here, just around the corner.  Other people of the same mindset You know that the true weapon of the 21-st century is cybersecurity. You see that the traditional banking should change forever. You trust robots. You see that blockchain is changing it all. And realize that good software is a true basis of competition in a modern world. Body: https://preview.ibb.co/chxOCc/photo_2018_02_20_22_59_35.jpg  We would like to start introducing our team members. Our CEO, Marius Parescius is a well-known European IT and cybersecurity professional, Lithuanian serial entrepreneur and mentor, IT counsellor to the Lithuanian Parliament, CEO, and founder of Baltic startup incubator and technology hub, Business Hive Vilnius (BHV).  But the most interesting fact about him, that in 1999 he launched the very first social network in Baltics (and, probably, in EU) ‚Äì Draugas.lt. It started as a dating site, and those time most of their users didn‚Äôt even have personal computers. So they sent their photos to Draugas.lt via post, Draugas team scanned the photos and put them on website.  The project is still one of the most popular online communities with millions of Lithuanian and Baltic people, around the world, having used it since its inception.

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: Talking about credibility and cybersecurity, you might have heard the story of Prodeum ICO. Briefly: a team that claimed to be Lithuanian stole 6M during the ICO and dropped their website, leaving the only word ‚Äúpenis‚Äù on it. There were plenty of articles about the issue in the media worldwide.  Marius and the team members of our cybersecurity startups, being both Lithuanians and blockchain experts, started to investigate the case. So they found out, that the team had nothing to do with Lithuania, the identities of founders were stolen, and the raised amount was only 6K euro. Moreover, they traced another scam ICOs of that team.  You can read an article about the case and investigation in our blog: https://medium.com/@baltic.fund/prodeum-scam-traces-are-linked-to-other-fraud-projects-and-have-nothing-to-do-with-lithuania-9fe11cf7ceea

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: When it comes to genuine Lithuanian ICOs, they are more than transparent and successful. Just imagine, that in less than 1 year teams based in Lithuania raised over 0,5B USD via ICOs. It‚Äôs quite an amount for such a small country. Most of these projects are fintech industry players. In 2017 the Bank of Lithuania introduced special banking and payment institution licenses for startups, that lead to 32 new fintech companies in the country during 2017. 80% of these companies, including Revolut, relocated to Lithuania from different parts of the world, including UK, Israel, India, China, etc. So meet the Amber Valley for IT-entrepreneurship ‚Äì the Baltics, and Lithuania, as a biggest Baltic state. Perhaps, you should think of it as the next destination for your startup.

Author: vasilyberdman
Title: üî•[ANN][ICO] Baltic Fund -INVEST IN PROMISING CEE & CIS STARTUPS AND ECOSYSTEMüî•
Body: https://preview.ibb.co/nR9hOH/Screen_Shot_2018_02_21_at_10_34_11.png  Let‚Äôs meet some startups from our accelerator Business Hive Vilnius. Primarily, we are focused on cybersecurity, Saas, AI, hardware and fintech. When it comes to hardware, we have very different startups, from robots to smart balance board, but the most disruptive one is Slydis. Slydis is a game-changer in the industry of personal mobility, it‚Äôs an electric, foldable, tracked, modular, jumping all-terrain vehicle.  Meet Slydis CEO ‚Äì Ramunas Stankevicius. https://www.linkedin.com/in/ram-stank-innovations/  https://image.ibb.co/nab7qx/Ramunas.jpg Ramunas is a brilliant engineer with several patented inventions. The idea of Slydis came to him several years ago, and after he spent thousands of hours on prototyping, developing and testing the components, he finally came to the right shape and is building a first full-size working model right now. The vehicle weight is about 50 kg, it‚Äôs foldable, which means, that you can put it in a boot of the car, it‚Äôs all-terrain and, what‚Äôs more important ‚Äì it‚Äôs going to be relatively cheap ‚Äì about 5000 euro.
